<div class="pageheader">Assignment 04.03 Simplify</div>


<div class="inlessontab">
<table  border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"> 
  <tr>
    <td>
	<p>Getting together to complete a task is a fact of life. In order to solve problems (algebra or otherwise), the act of simplifying before solving must be accomplished. </p> 
      <p>What if you were playing football and your team was down by 3, 30 seconds left on the clock, 20 yards to go, and it was 4th down? Even if you didn't understand the sport of football, you would say "the pressure is on!" At this point, there are many options: run, kick, pass, and a miracle. </p> 
      <p>With all these options and pressures, the best bet is to simplify the task into something that is workable, and then go out and solve your problem. </p> 
      <p>Let's <strong>simplify</strong> (huddle) first and then later we will be able to <strong>solve</strong>!!!
 </p>

<!--//special note-->
	  
	  <div class="note"> Before you can begin <strong>simplifying</strong>, you need to be familiar with some algebraic vocabulary words and phrases. Listed below are those words and phrases:
